Write Bash shell for following scenario.
• Launch an ec2 instance using Amazon Linux
  Install and run tomcat service.
• Write a bash shell script to validate if Tomcat running and if it's not start it. • Schedule the shell script to start tomcat service at 6AM every weekday.
Note: Participants in the Skills Assessment are required to utilize their personal GitHub accounts for the exercise and submit the repository link upon completion.
If you are unable to finish within the allotted 5 hours, you are permitted additional time to test your code. Please inform us when you are ready for the review process.